# Fixture: fm1-optional-filter-unbound
# Finding: Failure Mode 1 — OPTIONAL + FILTER on unbound variable
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §12.3.1 (OPTIONAL scoping), §17.3 (FILTER evaluation)
# Errata: SE-2
#
# Hypothesis: The outer FILTER references ?x which is only bound inside the
# OPTIONAL. When the OPTIONAL branch does not match, ?x is unbound for that
# solution. Per §17.3, evaluating (?x > 3) with an unbound ?x raises a type
# error, and a type error in FILTER causes the solution to be DISCARDED.
#
# Divergence: An implementation treating "unbound in FILTER" as `false`
# discards solutions that should survive (over-discard). One treating it as
# `true` retains solutions that should be discarded (over-include).
# Expected grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully; divergence is in
# evaluation semantics.

SELECT * WHERE {
  ?s <http://example/p> ?o .
  OPTIONAL {
    ?s <http://example/q> ?x .
    FILTER(?x > 5)
  }
  FILTER(?x > 3)
}
